RT @TraumaSpeaks: I think we often forget how we have a tendency to invalidate our own feelings because we’re taught how we need a reason o…

I challenge you to try to let that ego go & relinquish your pride when your loved one comes to you and tells you how they’re feeling. A lot of times they’re not attacking you, they’re just trying to be honest about how you hurt them. Love them . Listen. & try to not do it again.

And on the other side of that same coin, it’s so easy to be the person doing the invalidating. Sometimes we invalidate other people’s feelings unintentionally while trying to protect and defend ourselves. most of the time  that’s ego.

Feelings are not something that can always be proven with facts or evidence, if you feel it. You feel it. It’s real. Don’t let someone make you think your feeling isn’t “right” because they don’t understand it.

I know a lot of us have inhabited spaces where people always  combatted our feelings when we shared them, questioned the ‘truth’ of them, or in order for THEM to validate our feelings, they needed to understand. 

but I’m here to let you know that if you feel it. It’s REAL.
